    {
      "key": "90867e82-1b7b-4029-a08a-9f9c5174d8c3",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Besides defining classes and creating objects, software engineers write instructions to tell Java how to complete tasks. When we give instructions, we have to be as clear and concise as possible to ensure that Java completes the task the way we intend. We do this in our day-to-day lives as well.",
        "name": "Giving Instructions",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "90867e82-1b7b-4029-a08a-9f9c5174d8c3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7a39c692-da74-42dc-9da3-8deb42aa17bc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "47b4741a-63d8-42df-9559-44f9fbdd1576",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students work with their partner to write instructions that a GPS could use to direct a delivery driver to move from 1st Street and 1st Avenue to the customer located at 5th Street and 5th Avenue.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "There is space on the guided notes for students to write their instructions.\n\nHave students partner with another group to compare solutions. Call on groups to share their solutions and the similarities and differences they noticed in the different solutions."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "47b4741a-63d8-42df-9559-44f9fbdd1576",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7a39c692-da74-42dc-9da3-8deb42aa17bc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "de86f246-c214-4a07-b66f-738711fde78e",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "de86f246-c214-4a07-b66f-738711fde78e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7a39c692-da74-42dc-9da3-8deb42aa17bc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0f31c8d2-3aa6-40ec-83b6-5b1a495c29ff",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write instructions with their partner that a GPS could use to direct a bus driver to pick up riders from two bus stops, 5th Street and 5th Avenue and 5th Street and 3rd Avenue, and transport them to the library located at 2nd Street and 3rd Avenue."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0f31c8d2-3aa6-40ec-83b6-5b1a495c29ff",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7a39c692-da74-42dc-9da3-8deb42aa17bc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4e98f273-e0d2-4aa0-9ecc-f237d4ca3ffa",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4e98f273-e0d2-4aa0-9ecc-f237d4ca3ffa",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "137433f1-c7fc-4c4c-8251-e2c412145291",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Giving instructions to direct our delivery driver is similar to giving instructions in a program. We have learned how to create `Painter` objects and seen a few examples of programs where a `Painter` object is moving and painting in The Neighborhood. Let's take a closer look at how we give instructions to a `Painter` object.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "137433f1-c7fc-4c4c-8251-e2c412145291",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "69cee430-235b-48f6-94e5-0efe0535a9c9",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Painter Class Methods"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "69cee430-235b-48f6-94e5-0efe0535a9c9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "eb1f8ef9-2e30-4931-98a4-1d0fc3cd78d8",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify the methods used in the program and share ideas about what each method does. Students should also notice that each statement executes in the order written in the program. Students may wonder what might happen if the method calls were rearranged or how they might call other methods."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "eb1f8ef9-2e30-4931-98a4-1d0fc3cd78d8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7b6d6579-b5f6-4fc3-8e8e-8c9c9bccd449",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned that a class is like a blueprint that defines the things that an object should have. We also know that a class contains instructions for how to create an object from this blueprint. A class also defines the things that an object can do.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Painter Class Methods",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7b6d6579-b5f6-4fc3-8e8e-8c9c9bccd449",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "906ea4e7-cc2c-4538-a2d4-0db3b682cabc",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Recall *behavior* and define ***method***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Think of an object you might represent in a program, like a pet or a song. What behaviors would this object have? What methods would the class have to represent these behaviors?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share examples of objects and identify things the objects can do as examples of behaviors. Students suggest method names that would be in the class to represent these behaviors.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class.\n\nExample behaviors for a pet might include barking, playing, or eating. A `Pet` class might then have methods called `bark()`, `play()`, and `eat()` to represent these behaviors."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "906ea4e7-cc2c-4538-a2d4-0db3b682cabc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "23256f73-70e9-497c-9927-673f788ce0f5",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "23256f73-70e9-497c-9927-673f788ce0f5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "efed4d69-39bb-4ce2-b1ae-cf6b6808d826",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio to complete Levels 2 and 3. Students investigate the program by modifying the program as prompted and observing the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Painter Class Methods"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "efed4d69-39bb-4ce2-b1ae-cf6b6808d826",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e57439ce-8092-472b-83cc-235ee6c0ce39",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e57439ce-8092-472b-83cc-235ee6c0ce39",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2efd0563-2f3e-4689-95a6-561034563989",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Calling Methods*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2efd0563-2f3e-4689-95a6-561034563989",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "01d5342b-4724-4c0e-94f9-141e5466f4e6",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "01d5342b-4724-4c0e-94f9-141e5466f4e6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7db10eeb-c363-4301-8bfa-047c78ecd513",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Explain how to call a method:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Specify the name of the object\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Use the ***dot operator***\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Specify the name of the method followed by an empty set of parentheses\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 4 to complete Levels 4 and 5. Students complete a Check for Understanding on Level 4, then continue to complete a choice level on Level 5 to practice using some of the methods in the `Painter` class.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Calling Methods",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Painter Class Methods",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding and practice levels can be used as formative assessments to gauge understanding of vocabulary presented in the lesson and the syntax for calling methods."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7db10eeb-c363-4301-8bfa-047c78ecd513",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9931b1bb-6f39-4820-a900-0761f954bc92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "810d0670-d7a1-4a00-a342-defabbef09de",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students answer the self-check question by identifying the missing method call.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary",
        "name": "Fix the Code"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "810d0670-d7a1-4a00-a342-defabbef09de",
        "lesson_activity.key": "17a763a7-2288-4c1c-9bb1-c81efabf408a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c22aafcc-4502-4495-aae2-02356d2e8f04",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c22aafcc-4502-4495-aae2-02356d2e8f04",
        "lesson_activity.key": "17a763a7-2288-4c1c-9bb1-c81efabf408a"
