    {
      "key": "69175c2a-8a2a-4d95-87b3-68b4721f89fc",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot about getting input from the user and from files. ",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Glows, Grows, Want to Knows",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "69175c2a-8a2a-4d95-87b3-68b4721f89fc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8cbb1b37-05f6-40a7-8323-096533518493"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "87eb07f7-48c3-40a0-98ce-bdec4389aea1",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What was awesome about writing your code?*\n- *What is one action you can take to improve your code?*\n- *What questions do you have about today?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share aspects of their program they enjoyed or strengths of writing algorithms and identify areas of improvement to strengthen their programming skills. Students also share any questions or misconceptions they may have.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Glows, Grows, Want-to-Knows is a strategy to help students identify their strengths and areas of improvement and share any questions or misconceptions.\n\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "87eb07f7-48c3-40a0-98ce-bdec4389aea1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8cbb1b37-05f6-40a7-8323-096533518493"
      }
    },
