    {
      "key": "9a938abf-9e52-405c-b1e3-2da954cf9b3b",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We now know how to declare and initialize variables and modify the values that are assigned to a variable. We can use these variables with different operators to perform calculations on their values.",
        "name": "Arithmetic Operators",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9a938abf-9e52-405c-b1e3-2da954cf9b3b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a25478f0-a956-4053-b0c4-a898f5d20c96"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "976d4349-12ca-4325-8562-03bcb051ed4c",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce arithmetic operators.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Briefly explain the functionality of each arithmetic operator – addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, and modulus ( `%` ). You do not need to spend time explaining how each of these functions here since these are explored throughout the lesson."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "976d4349-12ca-4325-8562-03bcb051ed4c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a25478f0-a956-4053-b0c4-a898f5d20c96"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b85e0978-a0d0-4a51-9817-cfa60923b0db",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Where have you seen operators like this before? How did you use these operators?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recall arithmetic operators used in math class to perform calculations.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b85e0978-a0d0-4a51-9817-cfa60923b0db",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a25478f0-a956-4053-b0c4-a898f5d20c96"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e0bdf39c-e997-4b3e-92cf-5d19344b2f2a",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e0bdf39c-e997-4b3e-92cf-5d19344b2f2a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7c14fa7d-1a7a-4987-9993-b4c5985ad23a",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We can use these same operators in our programs to perform calculations. Today, we're going to explore how these operators are used and evaluated in Java.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7c14fa7d-1a7a-4987-9993-b4c5985ad23a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "29f1fa06-3246-4833-8f9c-caa64f9a79e4",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Operators and Expressions"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "29f1fa06-3246-4833-8f9c-caa64f9a79e4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ba08868e-169e-4292-86bf-1eaf675e79e4",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that dividing two `int` values results in a whole number. Students may wonder why the decimal portion is lost."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ba08868e-169e-4292-86bf-1eaf675e79e4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d02c51a6-fdaa-4879-8e7f-bb859555fcbf",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***expression*** and ***operand***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***compound expression***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio to complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Exploring Expressions",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Expressions"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d02c51a6-fdaa-4879-8e7f-bb859555fcbf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "97035519-36e7-4afa-a07d-bfca9884ddf0",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "97035519-36e7-4afa-a07d-bfca9884ddf0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ccf6c241-3a70-4a4e-bbcb-7ddf984b6205",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "One thing you might have noticed as you were exploring the program is that the way these operators work differs based on the data type.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Evaluating Expressions",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ccf6c241-3a70-4a4e-bbcb-7ddf984b6205",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "29fd8683-3406-4414-bb7d-c0a902009eb3",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How does the data type impact the way the expression is evaluated?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students note that using these operators with `int` and `double` values performs arithmetic calculations, while the `+` operator combines a `String` with the value to create one `String`. Students also realize that trying to use other operators with a `String` results in an error.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "29fd8683-3406-4414-bb7d-c0a902009eb3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "79b16e55-20e0-429d-ba14-bd448cfef3fb",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain how the value and type of the operand impact how the expression is evaluated.\n\n**Do This:** Demonstrate evaluating expressions and assigning the result to a variable:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Result is assigned to the variable on the left\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Variable is updated to the new result when used across multiple expressions\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate dividing two `int` values and define ***truncate***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students respond to the self-check question.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***concatenation***.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Point out the space inside the quotation marks with the text `\"Hello \"`. Note that not including the space would display `\"HelloWorld\"` instead of `\"Hello World\"`. Java prints exactly what is given inside quotation marks, so spaces should be included when needed to ensure the proper appearance of printed text."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "79b16e55-20e0-429d-ba14-bd448cfef3fb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "35a5d4cd-7307-4e14-bac6-2792ba68f021",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate using other operators with a `String`.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What happened when we tried to divide an `int` value by `0`? What about a `double`?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recall that dividing an `int` value by `0` resulted in an error, while dividing a `double` value by `0` resulted in `infinity`.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate dividing an `int` by `0` and explain the `ArithmeticException` error.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate dividing a `double` by `0` and explain why it is `infinity`.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "You do not need to go in depth about the way Java handles `double` values or the IEEE 754 standards. The goal is for students to understand the difference between dividing an `int` and a `double` by `0` and why this difference exists."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "35a5d4cd-7307-4e14-bac6-2792ba68f021",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3efc5c50-a55e-4950-82b4-2294dd58eae5",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Java also has additional operators that we can use to perform calculations and assign the result to a variable. Let's take a look at how these work.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Operators",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3efc5c50-a55e-4950-82b4-2294dd58eae5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "84762abd-03f2-4e14-94c3-87e0c619ca24",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5 and 6. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Operators"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "84762abd-03f2-4e14-94c3-87e0c619ca24",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "511b5d57-af3c-40eb-a938-5fce2dda61c0",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***compound assignment operator*** and demonstrate the examples.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate evaluating expressions using the mod ( `%` ) operator.\n\n**Do This:** Explain the order of operations:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Introduce the order of operations\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Respond to the self-check question\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *When would the mod ( `%` ) operator be useful?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest using the mod ( `%` )operator to determine if a number is a multiple of another number. Students note that the mod ( `%` ) operator could also determine if a number is even or odd.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "511b5d57-af3c-40eb-a938-5fce2dda61c0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a07d2c8f-9ac5-428c-a8e6-1fa7bd96eb84"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a1821fbe-2c74-4fcb-864f-0a9f4031d6fb",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot about working with variables and writing expressions! Let's take a moment to recap what we have learned.",
        "name": "Three W's",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a1821fbe-2c74-4fcb-864f-0a9f4031d6fb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0647c907-ba0a-4b1f-93f7-a674fafc4057"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0db84984-07a8-4ee3-a5f3-c15cf34089af",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did we learn today?*\n* *So what?*\n* *Now what?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students highlight the concepts and vocabulary they learned in this lesson, such as the mod ( `%` ) operator and compound assignment operator. Students also recall the result of dividing two `int` values and the difference between dividing an `int` and a `double` value by `0`.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0db84984-07a8-4ee3-a5f3-c15cf34089af",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0647c907-ba0a-4b1f-93f7-a674fafc4057"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "259af7c0-2470-46c4-b85b-1343bb42d401",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "259af7c0-2470-46c4-b85b-1343bb42d401",
