    {
      "key": "ac3c4676-2582-4880-9f3a-02f720dd1724",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot of new terms so far! Let's review some of these terms through a game of CS Pyramid.",
        "name": "CS Pyramid",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ac3c4676-2582-4880-9f3a-02f720dd1724",
        "lesson_activity.key": "207663fb-0edb-4ef5-a77f-158599114970"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f7cdd131-29f3-4b8f-9bef-9f4dbb769a01",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the instructions for playing CS Pyramid.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue the CS Pyramid activity, and direct students to play CS Pyramid. Click through the animated slide to display each pyramid, and direct students to switch roles with each new pyramid."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f7cdd131-29f3-4b8f-9bef-9f4dbb769a01",
        "lesson_activity.key": "207663fb-0edb-4ef5-a77f-158599114970"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a6835264-5dff-47ff-8daf-5a002c3b1fa5",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a6835264-5dff-47ff-8daf-5a002c3b1fa5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "82f74f20-c848-4276-9d3d-7c24de0d8889",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "In the previous lesson, we explored some of the methods in the `Math` class that are used to perform calculations. But that's not the only thing we can do with the `Math` class! Today, we'll explore how we can use the `Math` class to generate random numbers.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "82f74f20-c848-4276-9d3d-7c24de0d8889",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "929805a9-ac44-4887-ae94-4692496dd192",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Random Numbers"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "929805a9-ac44-4887-ae94-4692496dd192",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2eb99c75-1fb5-4f23-a834-a2a1f6e64f2e",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that the program displays a different number each time they run it and that the random number is always a `double` value. Students may wonder how to generate a random number within a specific range or how they could use random numbers in their programs."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2eb99c75-1fb5-4f23-a834-a2a1f6e64f2e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "86e348f3-e525-445e-8d3d-21a1c85f67f9",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce `Math.random()`.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Random Numbers"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "86e348f3-e525-445e-8d3d-21a1c85f67f9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e17f34c9-a35d-427e-bdb4-f4583be5e078",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "A random number between `0.0` and `1.0` is not always useful depending on the needs of our program. However, we learned about casting operators and ways to round numbers. These operators and strategies might be useful with `Math.random()` to get a random number within a specific range, like between `1` and `10`.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e17f34c9-a35d-427e-bdb4-f4583be5e078",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "39b66944-92c4-4504-899a-388e84b9f34a",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How could we write an expression using `Math.random()` to generate a random number within a specific range?*\n\nDiscussion Goal: Students suggest using casting operators to convert the value returned to an `int` value. Students recall adding `0.5` to round a number to the nearest integer and may suggest adding a value to the number generated to get a number within a specific range.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class.\n\nStudents may have other ideas about generating a random number within a specific range instead of or in addition to adding a value to the number returned from calling `Math.random()`. It is not important for students to reach this conclusion during this discussion, as they will test their ideas to reach this conclusion on the Investigate and Modify levels. The goal is for students to generate ideas about how to solve this problem."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "39b66944-92c4-4504-899a-388e84b9f34a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3dc9068f-6e2f-45c5-a0b8-5759315ae033",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio complete Levels 2 and 3. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Random Numbers"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3dc9068f-6e2f-45c5-a0b8-5759315ae033",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8c3e1f62-07e4-4c33-9ce5-18ca465ef8f0",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ask students to share how they generated a random number within a specific range on Level 2 and how this was similar and different from accessing a random element from a 1D array on Level 3."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8c3e1f62-07e4-4c33-9ce5-18ca465ef8f0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c957b5ff-9729-4582-9906-2ea75de04697",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Random Numbers*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c957b5ff-9729-4582-9906-2ea75de04697",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d79ecdc9-7e81-4203-b562-88e52c7a843a",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate generating a random number within a specific range using `Math.random()`.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students respond to the self-check question to choose the correct expression to access a random element from a 1D array.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain the solution."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d79ecdc9-7e81-4203-b562-88e52c7a843a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8360b1fa-06ee-4682-ba5a-085cd1edfde6",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Random numbers are useful for making our programs more interesting. We see randomness in many programs that we use every day.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Practice",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8360b1fa-06ee-4682-ba5a-085cd1edfde6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "11bbd4ac-f174-4a0a-ae52-d5057d37dd28",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What are programs that you use that have a random component?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share programs that they use that have a random component, such as enemies appearing in different locations in games or playing a music playlist on shuffle.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "11bbd4ac-f174-4a0a-ae52-d5057d37dd28",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cb20e360-a8cd-4cdb-b707-dbdf122aea1e",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 4 on Code Studio to complete Levels 4, 5, and 6. Students complete a Check for Understanding on Level 4, then complete choice levels on Levels 5 and 6 to practice generating random numbers and accessing random elements from a 1D array.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Using Random Numbers",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding is an AP-style multiple choice question that can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of generating random numbers within a specific range.\n\nThe practice levels can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of calling `Math.random()` and writing expressions to generate random numbers within a specific range."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cb20e360-a8cd-4cdb-b707-dbdf122aea1e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7da6776f-4291-4b9b-8c1c-3a70682d587c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "92136960-d76a-4547-9a09-0c6a93bede47",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "In a previous lesson, we chose datasets that we will use for our upcoming unit project. Let's start generating some questions we want to answer and visualize about our datasets.",
        "name": "Generating Questions",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "92136960-d76a-4547-9a09-0c6a93bede47",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a5398639-2c8f-43a3-9a80-b9150897e37b"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a3c9b92f-8137-4e52-b390-29b5e5e0d15f",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Return the Dataset Summaries handout to each student.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Dataset Summaries handout was collected from students at the end of the previous lesson. If you chose to have students keep these, prompt them to take them out for this activity.\n\nThis and upcoming activities help prepare students for the Abstract Data Art Project at the end of the unit. These activities are intended to give students time to choose their datasets, identify patterns, and consider how they will visualize the information so the project time can be dedicated to planning and developing the program and conducting code reviews."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a3c9b92f-8137-4e52-b390-29b5e5e0d15f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a5398639-2c8f-43a3-9a80-b9150897e37b"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "72252d5b-4cdc-4453-88b1-e8d57dd59ed6",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students generate questions they want to answer about their dataset.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share the questions they generated with a neighbor.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their chosen dataset and questions with the class.\n\nCollect the Dataset Summaries handouts to return to students in an upcoming lesson."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "72252d5b-4cdc-4453-88b1-e8d57dd59ed6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a5398639-2c8f-43a3-9a80-b9150897e37b"
      }
    },
