    {
      "key": "73bad4de-4424-4594-ac6e-7ad9a130ddfc",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you explored how to use the `substring()` method to extract specific parts of a `String`, and how it can be combined with other methods like `indexOf()` to analyze or manipulate text. These tools are powerful when working with any kind of user input, files, or program output.",
        "name": "Using String Methods",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "73bad4de-4424-4594-ac6e-7ad9a130ddfc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e8bcc86a-ddac-4ae3-9f8b-6ce95f7228be"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "21027401-36ee-43a1-83bb-a5e8401198f8",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Why do you think it's important that `String` objects are immutable? How might that affect how we use `substring()` or other methods in our programs?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students deepen their understanding of immutability and begin to appreciate how using methods like `substring()` can help solve problems like parsing, cleaning, or reformatting text, whether it's in a chatbot, form validator, or text game.\n\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
