    {
      "key": "2fd1a3b5-d278-4b3e-8803-43c2b290e58b",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *If you were writing a program to alphabetize these words, what order would you expect them to appear in? What makes it tricky?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recognize that computers use character codes (e.g., ASCII or Unicode), so capital letters come before lowercase. This sets up why `compareTo()` might return unexpected results if case isn't handled."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2fd1a3b5-d278-4b3e-8803-43c2b290e58b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1062292c-f8b7-46f7-8ccd-f3353e911d5f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cd9679aa-f51c-41b2-b590-1217243c801c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
