    {
      "key": "2eb8b21e-ea07-4356-b3d2-872737f30a4b",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students note that the `compareTo()` method returns a numerical value. Students also notice that the number correlates with whether the `String` comes before or after the other `String`. Students may wonder why the method doesn't return a `boolean` value instead of a number."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2eb8b21e-ea07-4356-b3d2-872737f30a4b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "028db449-d47b-488a-9d95-455d22b4e976"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "edbef87d-a26a-46be-8bb4-0441ec7b2012",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The `compareTo()` method can tell us whether a `String` comes before or after another `String`. This can be useful for situations like when we need to reorder a list in alphabetical order or to determine where we need to insert a new item in an existing list.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "The compareTo() Method",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "edbef87d-a26a-46be-8bb4-0441ec7b2012",
        "lesson_activity.key": "028db449-d47b-488a-9d95-455d22b4e976"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "18deaf3f-6172-4e95-9bdc-e2a2afd9f77c",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define ***lexicographical order***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: The compareTo() Method"
