    {
      "key": "9a66e22a-72bb-4e6e-aa6e-3da5dada7014",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did we learn today?*\n* *So what?*\n* *Now what?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share the concepts they learned from the lesson, including how to use the `compareTo()` method to compare two `String` objects. Students suggest problems where they might use methods in the `String` class in their Natural Language Processing projects and make predictions about upcoming lessons or problems.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary",
