    {
      "key": "5bdc8329-9301-4571-bb8c-c6fe8667bde1",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Your school's online coding club has given everyone a username that consists of their first name, followed by a dot, followed by their last name. For example, Grace Hopper's username would be Grace.Hopper. However, a software engineer accidentally deleted the data containing everyone's first and last name, leaving only the usernames of the club members.",
        "name": "Coding Club Usernames",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5bdc8329-9301-4571-bb8c-c6fe8667bde1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "66f442f2-c52e-421c-91d1-5fae8cdbe6c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8e2c26d7-4173-4f31-aa6f-0f17ad870423",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How can we retrieve a club member's first and last name from their username?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest using `indexOf()` to find the location of the dot. Students note that they can then use the two-parameter version of `substring()` to find the first name and then use the one-parameter version of `substring()` to find the last name.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8e2c26d7-4173-4f31-aa6f-0f17ad870423",
        "lesson_activity.key": "66f442f2-c52e-421c-91d1-5fae8cdbe6c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fc9290ff-5d96-4f25-8788-e552b8331111",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to review a solution.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What is the difference between the two versions of `substring()`?*\n* *How does Java know which one to use?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recall that the one-parameter `substring()` only specifies where to start and goes to the end, whereas the two-parameter version can specify both the start and end. Students identify that Java can differentiate between the two by the method signature.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Why do you think the designers of Java decided to give the two versions the same name?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest that the methods have the same name since they perform the same task but just give the user different options on the information required to perform the task."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fc9290ff-5d96-4f25-8788-e552b8331111",
        "lesson_activity.key": "66f442f2-c52e-421c-91d1-5fae8cdbe6c5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ccaac334-8e68-43b1-899c-034ea1a312e5",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ccaac334-8e68-43b1-899c-034ea1a312e5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "02b0a677-0c98-4210-a1b3-c08684d42ea4",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have used overloading when we write multiple constructors in a class. You can also have overloaded methods, which have some similarities to overloaded constructors. Today, we'll take a closer look at how overloaded methods are written and how these can be useful in our programs.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "02b0a677-0c98-4210-a1b3-c08684d42ea4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1e7cb7d0-493d-4dd4-a960-3666519502e4",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Overloaded Methods"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1e7cb7d0-493d-4dd4-a960-3666519502e4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1c7c9387-6add-4468-86ef-158c566702cd",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that the program has multiple methods with the same name but different parameters. Students also notice that they all perform the same task but with different inputs. Students may wonder how this is similar to overloaded constructors or how overloaded methods might be useful."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1c7c9387-6add-4468-86ef-158c566702cd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2bac2e72-74a1-4fa6-8841-129829760ed7",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to review overloading and overloaded constructors.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *Why did we use overloading with constructors?*\n* *How might overloading be helpful with methods?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students recall that orders can vary with the Joyful Pastries food truck. Some customers want to order just a standard dessert, while other customers want to customize their dessert. Students suggest that overloading methods make code more flexible for program requirements. The same task might require a different number of parameters, so having these methods share the same name also makes it easier to maintain.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Overloading",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Overloaded Methods"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2bac2e72-74a1-4fa6-8841-129829760ed7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "95339d59-5cde-42a2-8855-b8eb237f71ae",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ask additional guiding questions about what students noticed, such as:\n* *What is the difference between each version of the overloaded method?*\n* *Why do you think the different methods exist?*\n\nStudents should notice that the different versions of the methods take in different combinations of parameters and that the methods all perform the same task but give the user different options for performing the task."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "95339d59-5cde-42a2-8855-b8eb237f71ae",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9e593f16-0426-402d-ad55-38fecf517739",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain that methods are said to be overloaded when there are multiple methods with the same name but a different signature.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5 and 6. Students complete a Check for Understanding on Level 5, then continue to complete choice levels on Level 6 to practice writing overloaded methods.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Overloaded Methods",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Overloaded Methods"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9e593f16-0426-402d-ad55-38fecf517739",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e61521b4-7e6d-43ef-8ded-cbd4c3f4d5fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bd3f4e30-949a-4a43-a16a-7efc1af3e40a",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you learned that Java allows multiple methods to have the same name as long as they have different parameter lists. This is called method overloading, and it helps make code more readable and flexible.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bd3f4e30-949a-4a43-a16a-7efc1af3e40a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8eb78d79-270f-474e-bb1c-c2270a30264f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fe9c47ea-206d-4660-bb13-728840622817",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Why do you think it’s helpful for different methods that do similar things to share the same name?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students articulate the advantages of method overloading, such as clearer naming, code reusability, and being able to offer multiple ways to perform the same task depending on the inputs."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fe9c47ea-206d-4660-bb13-728840622817",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8eb78d79-270f-474e-bb1c-c2270a30264f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2daca09a-a491-4818-a3bb-8314711dcb66",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2daca09a-a491-4818-a3bb-8314711dcb66",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8eb78d79-270f-474e-bb1c-c2270a30264f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3d433616-4e3f-4fcd-b844-0dddc913a1d7",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3d433616-4e3f-4fcd-b844-0dddc913a1d7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8eb78d79-270f-474e-bb1c-c2270a30264f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "67d0776d-118c-4bcc-9fd5-e36b42ab9ea4",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "*Check For Understanding Question(s) and solutions can be found in each lesson on Code Studio. These questions can be used for an exit ticket.*",
        "name": "Assessment: Check for Understanding",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "67d0776d-118c-4bcc-9fd5-e36b42ab9ea4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8eb78d79-270f-474e-bb1c-c2270a30264f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "047c3125-0e84-42c2-b6f9-1846ed66942e",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The unit assessment project assesses proficiency in the knowledge and skills developed in this unit. It is completed in three class periods to plan and create the program, including writing a new subclass that extends `PainterPlus` with a new method. Students participate in planning and feedback activities to solve problems, reinforce software development practices and self-image as software engineers, and improve their programs.\n\nIf there is not enough time for the three-day project, a one-day option achieves the targeted learning objectives and goals. If using this option, refer to the [**Asphalt Art Project 1-Day Lesson Plan**](https://studio.code.org/s/csa1-2023/lessons/19). While the one-day option covers the learning objectives and goals, it shortens planning and reflection time. Consider this tradeoff when deciding which version to use."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "047c3125-0e84-42c2-b6f9-1846ed66942e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc20604-84cf-413e-b02a-998366201d03"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fe7e53e3-bded-49c1-ac92-b59ad03c465f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Asphalt art brightens communities, improves public safety, and inspires residents and visitors. Each project has a unique approach to revitalizing streets and parks and bringing communities together.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fe7e53e3-bded-49c1-ac92-b59ad03c465f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c7d00f52-d55a-4ead-8115-e5e48dd2accd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the video – *Unity and Safety Through Street Art in Norfolk, VA*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the examples of asphalt art.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What does this make you wonder about how you could create art in The Neighborhood?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students talk about using their `PainterPlus` class and developing additional subclasses to create asphalt art in The Neighborhood. Students present ideas of additional subclasses of `PainterPlus` they could create for elements in an asphalt art design because of limitations of the existing classes or to simplify complex components."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c7d00f52-d55a-4ead-8115-e5e48dd2accd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "641fe2c2-4beb-430c-b6c4-70c8584749d6",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Over the next few days, you will be developing a program to create asphalt art in The Neighborhood. You will need to use what you have created in this unit and create a new type of `Painter` to make your design.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Brainstorming and Planning",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "641fe2c2-4beb-430c-b6c4-70c8584749d6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5668ccb4-bc24-477b-9d8f-d2f062de4b93",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on pages 2 and 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5668ccb4-bc24-477b-9d8f-d2f062de4b93",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bb587c6d-0981-473c-9661-fe638dcaf335",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Introduce the steps students will take each day to complete the project:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Day 1 steps\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Day 2 steps\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Day 3 steps"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bb587c6d-0981-473c-9661-fe638dcaf335",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "96ccd912-48cf-44f1-84d8-c52f77222fba",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Before you begin writing your program, you first need to decide what you will create so you can plan your new subclass and methods to create your design.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "96ccd912-48cf-44f1-84d8-c52f77222fba",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "18b85af0-d5cc-4819-9579-ef45737a9504",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to sketch their asphalt art design, identify the subclasses they want to create, and write pseudocode for their methods to plan their project on the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Emphasize that the asphalt art design should be simple enough to create in the given timeframe while being complex enough to utilize the classes students have developed and highlight the need for a new class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "18b85af0-d5cc-4819-9579-ef45737a9504",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f65d811c-2527-48b9-a2fc-b710b608e7ea",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to develop their Asphalt Art Project.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Development",
        "progression_name": "Asphalt Art Project",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "You can refer students back to the [**Decomposition and Design**](https://studio.code.org/s/csa1-2023/lessons/13) lesson to recall how they broke down the murals to create the designs. Students may also want to save the `MuralPainter` to their Backpacks or copy some of its methods to use in the Asphalt Art Project."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f65d811c-2527-48b9-a2fc-b710b608e7ea",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6956fbcf-862e-41f8-8d35-892854475a5e",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our new subclass to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6956fbcf-862e-41f8-8d35-892854475a5e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e713aa2c-3b5f-42ef-9200-d7d2fec6a69c",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their new subclass to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e713aa2c-3b5f-42ef-9200-d7d2fec6a69c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6dad280c-06cc-4a60-a158-1dcd5eabe1f0",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You made a lot of progress on your project today! Let's take a moment to reflect on what you have accomplished so far and what you need to focus on next.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6dad280c-06cc-4a60-a158-1dcd5eabe1f0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b755470b-41e0-4a45-b251-09c65d4ffe6b",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the Day 1 Reflection prompt on the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can use the Day 1 Reflection as an optional completion assessment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b755470b-41e0-4a45-b251-09c65d4ffe6b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8bc6550d-e47e-4542-bad5-59e47f6dc904"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2a68df44-a42c-4727-8be3-ab6fd48d8a8c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Like in the examples we have seen in this unit, you are using computer science as a form of creative expression. You are also using your software engineering characteristics to create your programs.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2a68df44-a42c-4727-8be3-ab6fd48d8a8c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2f857c8d-84bc-45e0-ba8d-4d57ff7c9f98",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the prompt on the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2f857c8d-84bc-45e0-ba8d-4d57ff7c9f98",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "17affb98-37dc-41f4-9097-ab9ea77244b4",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the steps for Day 2 of the project.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Development"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "17affb98-37dc-41f4-9097-ab9ea77244b4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ca8a1500-f48b-4009-b342-0030af48ef97",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Continue to work on your Asphalt Art Project. Be sure to refer to the project requirements and rubric to make sure you include the necessary components.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ca8a1500-f48b-4009-b342-0030af48ef97",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b7fda5fe-74d0-4278-b3fe-6b7b021dcac1",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to continue developing their projects."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b7fda5fe-74d0-4278-b3fe-6b7b021dcac1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e9995a49-b3cd-44c7-9961-27d230eb335e",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our new subclass to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Code Review",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e9995a49-b3cd-44c7-9961-27d230eb335e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ab83f211-89e8-482b-bdd6-a5a75c7073a2",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their new subclass to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ab83f211-89e8-482b-bdd6-a5a75c7073a2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "28a622a6-bfd4-43b8-8f73-b64d8c0c2b3f",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we write new code, getting feedback from our peers is helpful to make sure we have met the requirements of the problem efficiently.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "28a622a6-bfd4-43b8-8f73-b64d8c0c2b3f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1d9891dd-05d6-45de-a23b-4d6d31d9ed6e",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to have students participate in the Code Review Call and Response.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to conduct a code review on their Asphalt Art Project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students may be at different points when it is time for the code review. Emphasize to students that their work does not need to be completed to get feedback. Remind students that the problem-solving and development process is iterative and that receiving feedback from peers while they are working can help give them additional insights, perspectives, and guidance.\n\nConducting code reviews on choice levels is slightly different than on single levels. To conduct a code review on a choice level:\n1. Students select the level they completed to request a code review on their work.\n2. Students return to the options by clicking the bubble at the top of the page.\n3. Students select the level their peers completed to give feedback on their work.\n\nTo review the feedback given on their work, students return to the options by clicking the bubble at the top of the page, then select the level they completed."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1d9891dd-05d6-45de-a23b-4d6d31d9ed6e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "aa0940e5-f559-4af0-b1bf-c4d5a5b3a83b",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You made a lot of progress on your project today! Let's take a moment to reflect on what you have accomplished so far and what you need to focus on next.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "aa0940e5-f559-4af0-b1bf-c4d5a5b3a83b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "12c56138-28e0-4e74-8871-60fab40b9b31",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the Day 2 Reflection prompt on the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can use the Day 2 Reflection as an optional completion assessment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "12c56138-28e0-4e74-8871-60fab40b9b31",
        "lesson_activity.key": "21b0657a-0e34-41a0-a042-daa6b3fe85ab"
      }
