    {
      "key": "c1fb31bb-dd71-4429-86ef-6fcd938ea16e",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Asphalt Art Project:** Use the rubric in the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide to assess the projects.",
        "name": "Assessment: Grading the Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c1fb31bb-dd71-4429-86ef-6fcd938ea16e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cf9e3a5e-fd95-4eb4-9fdc-da4075609c26"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e8dcc45d-7644-415e-b0f7-35d453811ef5",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Asphalt art brightens communities, improves public safety, and inspires residents and visitors. Each project has a unique approach to revitalizing streets and parks and bringing communities together.",
        "name": "Asphalt Art Projects",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e8dcc45d-7644-415e-b0f7-35d453811ef5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "87feb1b7-f538-41be-9c36-3b03ea0580da"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3ddcd62e-19a8-4395-93db-1e1544511f07",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the video – *Unity and Safety Through Street Art in Norfolk, VA*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the examples of asphalt art.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on pages 2 and 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3ddcd62e-19a8-4395-93db-1e1544511f07",
        "lesson_activity.key": "87feb1b7-f538-41be-9c36-3b03ea0580da"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "16252e58-c4f9-46dc-b119-7a6dbc51b873",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to sketch their asphalt art design and write pseudocode for a new method to plan their project on the Asphalt Art Project Planning Guide.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Brainstorming and Planning",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Emphasize that the asphalt art design should be simple enough to create in the given timeframe while being complex enough to utilize the classes students have developed and highlight the need for a new method."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "16252e58-c4f9-46dc-b119-7a6dbc51b873",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d06505a-31d9-4f59-8b1f-5db1316530b4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7faaa623-07ab-433d-b1b7-a52f481487c6",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to develop their Asphalt Art Project.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Development",
        "progression_name": "Asphalt Art Project",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "You can refer students back to the [**Decomposition and Design**](https://studio.code.org/s/csa1-2023/lessons/13) lesson to recall how they broke down the murals to create the designs. Students may also want to save the `MuralPainter` to their Backpacks or copy some of its methods to use in the Asphalt Art Project."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7faaa623-07ab-433d-b1b7-a52f481487c6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d06505a-31d9-4f59-8b1f-5db1316530b4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9b1807fc-0330-4181-b099-0c407fda1b7e",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our updated subclass to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9b1807fc-0330-4181-b099-0c407fda1b7e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d06505a-31d9-4f59-8b1f-5db1316530b4"
      }
    },
