    {
      "key": "10be35eb-3c4e-465e-983f-843186cc5609",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete a short end-of-unit survey. Although their answers are anonymous, the aggregated data will be available to you once at least five students have completed the survey.",
        "progression_name": "End of Unit Survey",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "We also have a teacher end-of-unit survey to learn more about how the unit went for you and your students. While students take their survey, please complete [**this end of unit survey for teachers**](https://studio.code.org/form/teacher_end_of_unit_survey?survey_data%5Bunit_number%5D=1) as well. Your feedback is valued and appreciated!"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "10be35eb-3c4e-465e-983f-843186cc5609",
        "lesson_activity.key": "699e35d6-1791-42a3-9087-c3af63a5e448"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "855e955f-200c-40d8-9d3c-107794fe79d9",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Describe one new thing you have learned about Java through this course.*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share concepts and skills they have learned in this unit.",
        "name": "Introduction to FRQs",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas on the Unit 1 Guide first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "855e955f-200c-40d8-9d3c-107794fe79d9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7cbe8c50-cb5c-493f-9ebf-d3cfe151cabc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "825c5cbe-d93f-42db-a744-c4c88d791b68",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We will learn about Free Response Questions, FRQs. We will practice an FRQ at the end of each unit to apply the programming skills you learn and solve problems similar to the FRQs on the AP CSA Exam.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "825c5cbe-d93f-42db-a744-c4c88d791b68",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7cbe8c50-cb5c-493f-9ebf-d3cfe151cabc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e9d8fdb4-9575-43dc-b929-be3456656ae8",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain the structure of an FRQ.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Upcoming units discuss the structure of the AP CSA Exam and FRQs in detail. If students ask questions about the AP CSA Exam, remind them that it is a long way off! Practicing several FRQs as a class better equips students to discuss the AP CSA Exam."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e9d8fdb4-9575-43dc-b929-be3456656ae8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7cbe8c50-cb5c-493f-9ebf-d3cfe151cabc"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f5132b91-60e3-4aeb-b850-e29fb5275743",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the lesson objectives and the Question of the Day.\n\n**Group:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the SpiralPainter FRQ handout.\n\n**Do This:** Explain the steps for the activity.\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Planning\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Around the World\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Reflection\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to the first page of the SpiralPainter FRQ handout. Have students annotate the question at the bottom of the page based on the annotation guide.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "FRQ Planning"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f5132b91-60e3-4aeb-b850-e29fb5275743",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5a0d59c7-b2f1-4b68-a4fa-099fc29c86f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9babf434-6dbb-4918-adeb-12fd5288eafb",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *Which parts of the problem did you highlight pink or underline?*\n* *Can someone help explain these words or concepts?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share words and concepts they didn't understand and discuss their meanings.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *Which parts of the problem did you highlight blue or star?*\n* *Which parts did you highlight orange or box?*\n* *How do you expect you will use these pieces of information while coding?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify components of the problem that will help develop the solution."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9babf434-6dbb-4918-adeb-12fd5288eafb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5a0d59c7-b2f1-4b68-a4fa-099fc29c86f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "12a1476a-4113-444a-bfac-2e81f248df98",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to complete the Around the World activity with their partners.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Around the World",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If there are fewer than six pairs, students may need to move on to complete an additional section before finding a group for a signature.\n\nIf students are stuck on a station, suggest:\n* Writing comments for each \"Do this\" item.\n* Returning to the manipulatives and tracing through their pseudocode again.\n\nDifferentiation Suggestions:\n* Tell pairs who need more time to obtain two signatures instead of three. Have these students focus on completing the constructor and one of the methods.\n* Encourage those who finish early to serve as reviewers."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "12a1476a-4113-444a-bfac-2e81f248df98",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5a0d59c7-b2f1-4b68-a4fa-099fc29c86f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c2026b28-5e66-488f-9e38-3376667a74b3",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Great work, everyone! Let's take a look at one potential solution to this problem. You might have a different approach, and that's ok! There are often multiple ways to achieve the same goal.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c2026b28-5e66-488f-9e38-3376667a74b3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5a0d59c7-b2f1-4b68-a4fa-099fc29c86f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ccf7e678-4fe9-40b0-90cf-fe562c1815ac",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Discuss possible solutions for each station:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Station A solution\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Station B solution\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Station C solution",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The SpiralPainter FRQ handout can be used as an optional formative assessment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ccf7e678-4fe9-40b0-90cf-fe562c1815ac",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5a0d59c7-b2f1-4b68-a4fa-099fc29c86f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "87a51db2-a496-4eef-b75d-9ea78bde6681",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What is your first impression of an FRQ?*\n* *What knowledge and skills did you use that you learned in this unit?*\n* *What were you confident about? What would you like to practice?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their first impressions of an FRQ and connect the concepts they learned in the unit to those assessed. Students share what they were confident about and any areas they need additional practice.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson and the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Closing the Loop"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "87a51db2-a496-4eef-b75d-9ea78bde6681",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cd90ff7d-e0b6-48f9-a3e4-3e443a83c271"
      }
    },
